  "prompt": "Can I be pregnant while having a missed period?",
  "response": "Yes, a missed period can be a sign of pregnancy. When a woman becomes pregnant, her body starts producing the pregnancy hormone hCG (human chorionic gonadotropin), which can cause the uterine lining to remain intact rather than shedding during a menstrual period. \n\nHowever, a missed period doesn't always mean you're pregnant. There are other possible reasons for a missed period, including stress, significant weight changes, hormonal imbalances, and certain medical conditions. \n\nIf you think you might be pregnant, the most reliable way to find out is to take a pregnancy test. These tests detect the presence of hCG in your urine. If the test is positive, it's a good idea to follow up with a healthcare provider to confirm the pregnancy and start prenatal care.",
